Dscription
======================================================

This is a OAuth example for Yahoo! API using PHP Session



License
======================================================

No License, just for fun.



GET Yahoo! SDK
======================================================

* Get SDK form: http://developer.yahoo.com/social/sdk/
* Download the Yahoo! PHP SDK 1.0
   * SRC: https://github.com/yahoo/yos-social-php5/
   * ZIP: https://github.com/yahoo/yos-social-php5/zipball/master



Setup SDK
======================================================

Suppose downloaded sdk form github is *master.zip*

$ unzip master.zip
$ mv yahoo-yos-social-php5-d34814f/lib/Yahoo/ ./ 
$ mv yahoo-yos-social-php5-d34814f/lib/OAuth/ ./



Result dir
======================================================

- YahooOAuth.inc
- SessionClean.php
- OAuthExample.php
- GET_APITest.php
- Yahoo/
	- YahooCurl.class.php
	- YahooOAuthAccessToken.class.php
	- YahooOAuthApplication.class.php
	- YahooOAuthApplicationException.class.php
	- YahooOAuthClient.class.php
	- YahooOAuthRequestToken.class.php
	- YahooYQLQuery.class.php
- OAuth/
	- OAuth.php



Confit OAuth keys
======================================================

* Edit YahooOAuth.inc

	$CONSUMER_KEY = "<your consumer key>"
	$CONSUMER_SECRET = "<your sunsumer secret>";
	$APPLICATION_ID = "<your application id>";
	$CALLBACK_URL = "http://<your validated host>/OAuthExample.php";



Run
=====================================================

1. Open your browser
2. Input url: http://<your validated host>/OAuthExample.php



